a_n=\sum_{k=1}^{n} \frac{1}{n+k}=\frac{1}{n+1}+\frac{1}{n+2}+\dots+\frac{1}{2n}
\lim a_n
\sum_{k = 1}^{n}\frac{1}{k} - \log{n} \rightarrow \gamma
\sum_{k = 1}^{2n}\frac{1}{k} - \log{2n} \rightarrow \gamma
\sum_{k = n+1}^{2n}\frac{1}{k} - \log{2n} +\log{n} \rightarrow 0
\sum_{k = n+1}^{2n}\frac{1}{k} \rightarrow \log{2}
\dfrac 1{n+k}
\dfrac {1}{n} \dfrac {1}{1+\frac k n}
\sum_{k=1}^{n}\frac1{n+k}=\left(\sum_{k=1}^{2n}\frac1k\right)-\left(\sum_{k=1}^{n}\frac1k\right)\simeq\ln2n-\ln n=\ln\frac{2n}n=\ln2.
\sum_{k=1}^{n}\frac1{n+k}=\frac1n\cdot\sum_{k=1}^{n}\frac1{1+\frac kn}=\int_0^1\frac{dx}{1+x}=\ln(1+x)|_0^1=\ln2.
